result.execSummary:
The defendant Mitchell Ryan Engebretson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Mitchell Ryan Engebretson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Mitchell Ryan Engebretson was found guilty of Intent.Dispose Methamphetamine Waste [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.67(2)(b).
  • Mitchell Ryan Engebretson was found guilty of Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(<=3g) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)1.

records.addlTxt:
Case called at 9:42 a.m.
Defendant Mitchell Ryan Engebretson in court with attorney David William Franker.  Katherine M. Findley appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Probation Agent Roger McDermott in court. 

D.A. Findley informs Court an amended information will be filed today and parties will proceed with plea and sentence on the amended charges.
Atty Franker is in agreement.
State files amended information.  Atty Franker waives reading of the same.
Defendant enters plea of "no contest" to Counts 1 and 2 of the amended information.
Court questions Defendant re: his plea and waiver of rights.
All parties stipulate that there is factual basis.
Court also questions Atty Franker re: his client's plea and waiver of rights.
State consents to waiver of Jury Trial.  Court  accepts plea as entered freely, voluntarily, and knowingly.  Court finds the defendant guilty on both counts.
Parties are prepared for sentencing.  Court takes recess at 10:19 am.
Court back in session at 10:38 am.  Court has been provided with a Plea Agreement.  Court is not bound by the Plea Agreement and this is explained to the defendant.  Defendant understands this and it has no effect on his plea.  All parties have received the PSI from DOC.  Atty. Franker has some corrections.  Atty. Franker explains the corrections that he feels should be noted.    Atty Findley responds to corrections that Atty Franker stated to the Court.  Atty Findley addresses the Court as to sentencing.  Atty. Franker addresses the Court as to sentencing.  Neither party requests testimony from the author of the PSI - Roger McDermott.  Court asks the defendant is he wishes to address the Court.  The defendant addresses the Court.  Atty Franker informs the Court that Ms Wyman(defendant's mother) wishes to address the Court.   Court asks the defendant is he wishes to tell the Court anything else before sentence is imposed.  
Court imposes for Count 1 - 5 years incarceration and 2 mon extended supervision 
Conditions:  Defendant shall pay costs in the amount of $268.00.  If not paid upon discharge a judgment will be entered.  Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcoholic veverages or nonprescription controlled substances, or any prescription medicine for which the defendant does not have a current prescription.  Defendant shall not enter into any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale of alcoholic beverages.  Defendant shall consent to a reasonable request of a law enforcement officer, based on probable cause, to submit to a breath, blood, salive, or urine test for purposes of determining the quantity of alcohol or drugs in defendant's breath, blood, saliva, or urine.  Defendant shall abide by all other terms and conditions of probation deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.  Defendant shall participate in any and all counseling deemed appropriate by the DOC.  Defendant shall undergo an alcohol assessment and follow any recommendations.  
Count 2 Sentence withhled and defendant placed on probation for 5 years consecutive to Count 1.  Conditions same as in Count 1. 
Court in recess at 11:50 am.  Defendant should report to the Laf. Co Jail by 6:00 pm on Monday 10/3/16.   Parties agree that defendant must report today to the Lafayette County Jail.   Court orders that bail is revoked and he be remanded to the custody of the Sheriff forthwith.
Sentencing hearing on September 30, 2016 at 09:00 am.
